saveTaskForUser

public boolean saveTaskForUser(User user,
                               Task task)
If the provided task object has no URI, this function will post a request with the server to create a new task, receive a reply with the assigned URI, and store in on the database. If there is an URI, it will post a request to overwrite the resource with the new data.

Parameters:
task - Task object with the new data to store
Returns:
Returns false if request was unsuccessful, call getLastError() to find out what went wrong
